I did the TC and FG portions (and the random turn-in stuff in between) today... and I found information that doesn't match exactly with the guide.  I also received a few items from Draz Nurakk's corpse in FG that I'd not heard of before.  Here's what happened...<br>
<br>
In TD, upon turning in the seal to the scout, the weak Draz spawned.  I killed him away from the ruin.  Immediately, the level 55 image (and *only* the level 55 image) spawned and charged me.  It was definitely aggressive.  I was not in wolf form - other group members were (hmm).  At this point, it was the only image up.  I didn't time it, but one by one the other images started to spawn.  We killed the level 55 one, and there were 4 of the level 53 images up.  We pulled and killed the first level 53 one - which was scowling at me immediately, when I was out of aggro range.  Now, the last one had spawned, leaving the last 4 level 53 images.  We pulled one, and *while we were fighting it*, another all of the sudden ran in.  About 15 seconds later, a 3rd one ran in, and we had 3 on us.  Two of the three were unmezzable.  There are now at *least* two unmezzables.  We fought off the two unmezzable ones, and then got the one that had been mezzed.  It was unslowable (normal), but it definitely flurried me a few times.  Here's the fun part... while we're doing this, apparently the raptors on the island respawned (we cleared them before starting) - but when we went to find our last image, it was busy fighting two raptors.  Fortunately, with help from us, it killed them, and then attacked us - we finished it off.  I'm glad that we found it - I *think* it could have won the fight with two raptors by itself... but if anyone gets in this position with all of the raptors ganging up on an image when it's out of sight behind that ruin wall... well, it could be disappointing, to say the least.<br>
<br>
That seemed different than what I'd seen in the guide.  The rest of it seemed pretty similar to what was in the guide.  Pretty much the only thing that worked on Draz was the special claws, and magic DD's, and poison dots (didn't try disease).  It had very high fire and cold resistances.  Magical dots (enchanter torment of argli and asphixiate) stuck sometimes, after tash.  Magic based DD's seemed to work okay.  Venom of the Snake stuck more often than not.  Pets cannot hurt it.  It was very resistant to slow (after tash, my 60 enchanter failed about 80% of the time) but it did slow.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to post what I saw in TD - it seemed strange.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kelric<br>
